50|$|For minors {{under age}} 12, {{there is never}} prosecution. For those aged 12 to 17, {{juvenile}} court is in charge. The most severe punishment by juvenile court is imprisonment till the age of 20. But when aged 16 or 17 and suspected of severe offences, the juvenile court can decide to transfer to Correctional Court (for murder cases <b>Court</b> <b>of</b> <b>Assize).</b> The most severe punishment by <b>Court</b> <b>of</b> <b>Assize</b> when aged 16 or 17 (when crime is committed) is 30 years' imprisonment (eligible to apply for parole after serving 15 years).|$|R
